  "prompt": "What Pok\u00e9mon hatches from Eggs in Pok\u00e9mon GO?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon GO, the Pok\u00e9mon that hatch from Eggs can vary based on the type of Egg: 2 km, 5 km, 7 km, 10 km, and 12 km Eggs. Each type of Egg contains a different pool of potential Pok\u00e9mon. As this information can change with updates and events, here is a general overview based on typical Egg hatches as of October 2023:\n\n### 2 km Eggs\nCommon Pok\u00e9mon that can hatch from 2 km Eggs include:\n- Pikachu\n- Sunkern\n- Magikarp\n- Pidgey\n- Cleffa\n- Igglybuff\n\n### 5 km Eggs\nCommon Pok\u00e9mon that may hatch from 5 km Eggs include:\n- Snubbull\n- Trapinch\n- Porygon\n- Surskit\n- Zigzagoon\n\n### 7 km Eggs (often includes gift Eggs)\nPossible hatches from 7 km Eggs often include:\n- Alolan variants (like Alolan Meowth)\n- Regional exclusives\n- Pok\u00e9mon like Dedenne, Galarian Meowth, and more.\n\n### 10 km Eggs\nPok\u00e9mon that usually hatch from 10 km Eggs include:\n- Kangaskhan\n- Chansey\n- Dratini\n- Larvitar\n- Gible\n\n### 12 km Eggs\nTypically, the 12 km Eggs include:\n- Legendary Pok\u00e9mon like the Celestial Legendaries\n- Pok\u00e9mon like Deino, and Galarian Zigzagoon.\n\nKeep in mind that the specific Pok\u00e9mon available in Eggs can change due to game events, seasonal changes, and updates. Always check the latest announcements from Niantic for the most current information on hatching Pok\u00e9mon in Pok\u00e9mon GO.",
